Title: Analysis of the  Dutch Disease  effect and public financial management in Mongolian economy
Abstract: This paper aims to diagnose the Mongolian economy for evidence of the  Dutch Disease  by applying a vector auto-regression model for the period 1993 2016 under the current market-based regime including resource-booming times. The results indicate a strong possibility that the Mongolian economy has been suffering from Dutch Disease through resource movement and spending effects: the mining boom crowds out manufacturing and fails to contribute to capital accumulation facilitating diversification. Policy implications for Mongolian public financial management suggest using part of the resource fund for public investment in education, health and infrastructure to promote industrial diversification.
