Title:A gravity model for international trade and conflict 
Abstract:This  paper  investigates  the  nexus  between  conflict  and  trade  using  data  from  77 countries.  For this  purpose,  it  puts  forward  a  gravity  model  that  is  augmented  with interstate   conflict   casualties.   In   order   to   overcome   statistical   problems   related   to heteroscedasticity  and  the  omission  of  the  extensive  margin  (the  zero  observations),  the gravity  modelis  estimated  using  a  Poisson  Pseudo-Maximum  Likelihood  method  (PPML). The  model  suggests  a  downward  impact  on  trade  that  affects  all  sides  of  the  conflict, whether  they  suffer  casualties  or  deal  them.  However,  said  impact  remains  small,  which hints  that  even  before  direct  conflicts  occur,  the  involved  countries  are  less  likely  to  have significant trade flows. 
